# TypeScript for components

- Write new source files as `.ts` or `.tsx`, not `.js` or `.jsx`.
- When editing component JavaScript, migrate to TypeScript in the same change when practical.
- Prefer explicit props and return types for exported components/hooks.
- Do not use `any`; use precise types or `unknown` plus narrowing.
- If a temporary `any` is unavoidable, add a one-line TODO with follow-up intent.
- Keep runtime behavior unchanged during type-only refactors unless explicitly requested.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
type Props = any;

// ✅ GOOD
type Props = {
  title: string;
};
```
